{"_meta": {"upstream": "w1hkj/fldigi 4.1.23 @ 61b97f413", "files": ["src/mfsk/mfskvaricode.cxx (varienc/varicode[] table)", "src/filters/viterbi.cxx (encoder(7,0x6d,0x4f) — NASA K=7 rate-1/2, mfsk.h:54-56)", "src/mfsk/interleave.cxx (interleave(symbits,depth) diagonal (de)interleaver)", "src/misc/misc.cxx:123 (grayencode — XOR cascade, the gray->binary map)", "src/mfsk/mfsk.cxx:919-953 (sendsymbol/sendbit/sendchar TX chain)"], "cmd": "bash scratch/refvectors/build_mfsk.sh", "note": "Per representative submode: 'varicode' = MFSK Varicode bits for 'msg' (self-framed, no separator); 'coded' = streaming K=7 (0x6d/0x4f) conv-encoder output, 2 bits per varicode bit (poly1 parity then poly2); 'symbols' = post-interleave symbits-bit values fed to sendsymbol (interleave(symbits,depth,FWD)); 'tones' = grayencode(symbol) tone indices on the wire. Data portion only — the STX/EOT/preamble framing envelope + AFC are deferred (loopback + #[ignore] cross-decode gate), matching the Phase-9 DominoEX precedent. omnimodem's modes::mfsk + fec::interleave::MfskInterleaver reproduce 'symbols'/'tones' byte-for-byte; the bit-domain stages are also plain lib unit tests since CI does not enable testutil."}}
